data.meta_description: Trey Zuhn III (60) OL - 2023 (SOPHOMORE): Started all 13 games at left tackle and was one of two offensive linemen to start each game ... Made the start at M...
data.text:
2023 (SOPHOMORE): Started all 13 games at left tackle and was one of two offensive linemen to start each game ... Made the start at Miami, while the offensive line allowed only 1.0 sack in 53 pass attempts ... Assisted the offense to a season-high 399 yards passing on 40 attempts, while allowing only 2.0 sacks in the win against ULM ... Helped clear the way for the Aggie rushing attack to over 200 yards in wins over Auburn (209), Arkansas (204) and Mississippi State (246) ... Protected the quarterback as a member of the offensive line that allowed 2.0 sacks-or-less in nine games ... Helped the offense record its third 300-plus yard passing game with 305 yards at Ole Miss, while the offensive line allowed only 1.0 sack ... Made the start at the Texas Bowl as the offense passed for 372 yards, while the offensive line allowed 2.0 sacks in 35 pass attempts ... Received the Offensive Trenches Award at the annual team banquet.

2022 (FRESHMAN): Started at left tackle in all 11 games he played in ... Earned the offense's Attitude and Most Improved awards at the annual team banquet.

2021 (REDSHIRT): Played in four games ... Received the Freshman Academic Award at the annual team banquet.

HIGH SCHOOL: Rated as a 4-star prospect and a top-30 offensive tackle by 247 Sports, Rivals and ESPN ... Coached by Jeff Fulton at Fossil Ridge High School ... Was a two-sport athlete in high school that participated in track & field (shot put, discus) in addition to football.
